FT  29 JUL 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fleece wool prices increased at the opening Australian wool sale in Sydney
this week, and the Wool Corporation's market indicator at 459 cents a kg.
was 15 cents higher then at the closing sale of the 1992/93 season at the
end of June. The Increase has been expected after Chinese business in
Australia and elsewhere, following a currency revaluation. This helped to
bring out more business from other wool buyers. European interest rate
reductions are seen as helpful especially if they lead to improved trading
there.
