<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 93 / International Company News: Charge helps push Noranda into
red
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NORANDA, the big Canadian resource group, has run into the red with a
first-half loss of CDollars 30m (USDollars 23.4m), or 32 cents a share,
against profits of CDollars 49m, or 10 cents, last time, writes Robert
Gibbens.
The group has been hit by declining commodity prices and a CDollars 30m
charge on the sale of its 49 per cent stake in MacMillan Bloedel.
Revenues were CDollars 2.6bn, down from CDollars 4.3bn, reflecting the
MacMillan Bloedel disposal.
The second-quarter loss this year equalled 7 cents a share against a profit
of 9 cents. The lower Canadian dollar and lower interest expense partly
offset weak prices for metals, papers and oil and gas.
The sale of the MacMillan stake has reduced Noranda's long-term debt to
CDollars 2.9bn.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Noranda Inc.
    Loblaw Companies Inc.
    Torstar Corp.
    Fletcher Challenge Canada.
    Falconbridge Minerals.
    Falconbridge Gold Corp.
    Kinross Gold.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>CAZ  Canada.
