FT  29 JUL 93 / International Company News: Anheuser Busch increases
dividend
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ANHEUSER-BUSCH, the biggest US brewer, yesterday posted essentially flat
second-quarter net income on sales which edged 1.3 per cent higher and said
it would raise its quarterly dividend by 12.5 per cent.
For the 1993 second quarter, the company had net income of Dollars 308.6m on
sales of Dollars 3.43bn, compared with earnings of Dollars 308.4m on sales
of Dollars 3.38bn a year earlier. Fully diluted earnings per share rose 4.7
per cent to Dollars 1.11 from Dollars 1.06. There were fewer shares
outstanding in the latest quarter.
The company also said it would increase its quarterly dividend on common
stock to 36 cents a share from 32 cents.
For the first half, the company had net income of Dollars 502.7m, or Dollars
1.80 on sales of Dollars 6.3bn. A year earlier, Anheuser-Busch earned
Dollars 446.8m, or Dollars 1.54, in the first six months on sales of Dollars
6.41bn. Last year's earnings included charges of Dollars 76.7m for
accounting changes.
During the second quarter, the company's market share rose to 41.9 per cent
compared with 41.6 per cent a year ago.
