<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Andrews Sykes warns on outcome
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Andrews Sykes fell 17p to 100p after the industrial services
company warned that first-half results would be 'significantly below those
of last year.'
Mr David Hubbard, chairman, told the annual meeting that the expected upturn
in demand had not materialised in the first quarter to June 30.
</TEXT>
