FT  29 JUL 93 / Observer: Cayzer-speak
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The plebs rarely attend AGMs of Caledonian Investments, the publicly quoted
arm of Lord Cayzer's family fortune. But yesterday's affair was even more
rarefied than usual. What on earth was John Kemp-Welch, joint senior partner
of Cazenove, going on about when he lapsed into Latin during the customary
vote of thanks?
Cayzer family retainers note that the last time it happened was in 1987 when
Kemp-Welch uttered a dictum which translated roughly as 'the past has been
magnificent but let us hope that the best is yet to come'.
But what inspired his latest outburst, ending with the immortal words 'nihil
adhuc non vidistia' - was the Wykehamist broker reflecting the wisdom of
Pliny, Horace . . . or whom?
More like Ronald Reagan, Kemp-Welch admits.
