FT  29 JUL 93 / Letter: Swings and roundabouts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Ms ANN THWAITE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Ms Mary Campbell (Letters, July 27) claims that only rich (uncaring)
parents would benefit from tax deductable child care. I am not rich but I
can see the immediate benefit of paying less tax, or of being taxed only
once. My salary is taxed, I pay the child minder and then she is taxed, so
the money I earn is being taxed twice. A bit like VAT really, isn't it? And
does Ms Campbell truly believe that the government would increase child
benefit at a time when it is looking at ways to reduce its social security
budget?
Surely this argument is all swings and roundabouts anyway. Either the
government loses/pays more money and working parents benefit or working
parents continue to pay more money and the government benefits. Ann Thwaite,
11 Roden Gardens,
Croydon CR0 2DQ
