FT  29 JUL 93 / People: Finance moves - Henderson Administration
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In the latest of many management changes at fund managers HENDERSON
ADMINISTRATION, John Hughes, the board member responsible for
administration, has resigned. A spokesman on behalf of the company said that
his job had changed, and been enlarged, since the recent acquisition of
Touche Remnant. 'There were lengthy discussions about his role and about job
satisfaction. But it didn't work out, unfortunately for him,' the spokesman
said.
Hughes, 48, had been on the board since 1988 and had joined the company a
year earlier. Between 1984 and 1987 he had been systems director at BZW, and
for the previous decade he had worked in the marketing department of Rank
Xerox.
Tony Solway, director of systems, is acting head of administration while the
board decides what will happen to the post.
