FT  29 JUL 93 / Gambling on aid
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ramsgate in Kent, on the Isle of Thanet - which includes the other seaside
towns of Margate and Broadstairs - is the only area in the south-east to
gain full development rather than intermediate area status, which puts it on
a par with areas such as Glasgow, Liverpool, Barnsley and Hartlepool. Thanet
has not received aid in the past and there is a lack of familiarity with the
procedures involved. Thanet District Council is telling companies which want
advice on how to get aid to contact either the East Kent Initiative in
Dover, which made the bid for assisted status on behalf of the area, or the
DTI directly. Hotels and tourist services, on which Thanet's economy has
traditionally depended, are eligible for aid.
