FT  29 JUL 93 / NBC pays record sum for Olympics
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BARBARA HARRISON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ATLANTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NBC, the US television network, has agreed to pay a record Dollars 456m for
US broadcast rights to the 1996 summer Olympics in Atlanta, despite losing
Dollars 100m on the games in Barcelona. It beat bids of about Dollars 450m
from ABC, regarded as the front-runner, and Dollars 415m from CBS.
