Ebersol, president of NBC Sports, said he expected to make a profit and was
confident enough to offer the International Olympic Committee and the
Atlanta one a share of revenues if advertising sales exceeded Dollars 615m.
NBC's bid did not include a cable partner. Turner Broadcasting System, based
in Atlanta, declined to put up any money for the rights fee.
The European broadcasting rights were sold earlier this year for Dollars
250m to the European Broadcasting Union.
