<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 93 / EC fails to agree loan scheme
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission yesterday failed to agree a loan scheme to help
steel-makers establish a Dollars 1bn (Pounds 670m) restructuring fund,
dealing another blow to the EC's steel rescue plan, Reuter reports from
Brussels.
Several commissioners questioned the legal basis which would be used to
implement the plan, a Brussels spokesman said.
