<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUL 93 / International Company News: Advance Bank ahead 25% to
ADollars 56m for year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ADVANCE BANK, the Australian bank, reports a 25 per cent earnings gain to
ADollars 55.9m (USDollars 38m) for the year ended May. The dividend is going
up from 38 cents to 50 cents a share.
Bad and doubtful debt expense was reduced from ADollars 36m to ADollars
27.5m, and net non-performing loans fell from ADollars 116.0m to ADollars
83.2m. Gross assets grew from ADollars 8bn to ADollars 9.2bn.
Mr Jim Service, chairman, described the result as pleasing in difficult and
competitive conditions.
